The paper presents a text analysis tool set that automatically clusters texts, extracts named entities, and generates hyperlinks. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category (cs.CL). Additionally, the tool set uses machine learning to learn relationships between entities, which indicates that it may also belong to the Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper's focus on clustering and linking entities suggests that it may also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper's emphasis on navigating and exploring document collections suggests that it may also belong to the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
